oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Hall of Fame and Country Music Show at Monroe's Bluegrass Musicland Park (16650)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Monroe, Bill, 1911-1996; Metal photoplates;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two color half sheet (red and black on white) announcing the Hall of Fame and Country Music Show with Bill Monroe, Ernest Tubb, Jack Greene, Jeanne Seely, Pee Wee King, Jimmy C. Newman, Collins Sisters, James Monroe, Wendy Bagwell and Sunliters, Redd Stewart and Carl and Pearl Butler at Monroe's Bluegrass Musicland Park on July 4-6. Poster features metal photoplates of Bill Monroe, Ernest Tubb, Jack Greene, Jeanne Seely, Pee Wee King, Jimmy C. Newman, Collins Sisters, James Monroe, Redd Stewart and Carl and Pearl Butler. To view the paperwork associated with this poster, see https://digi.countrymusichalloffame.org/digital/collection/hatch3/id/20530.
